    <div class="article comment" id="cid-1634740">
      <p class="text">Here's how I do it: I make a normal batch (I never use egg whites), then after taking it out of the oven I take another baking sheet and put that directly on top of the cooling granola batch. I usually weigh it down with a couple of cast iron pans. The pressure helps it stick together. Then when it's cool, I break it apart! Easy peasy!</p>
      <div class="footer meta">
